args:
When the prince's party and Nedrick finally
clash, our heroes find themselves struggling 
in the face of his overwhelming power. But
then something strange happens to Nedrick,
causing him to flee in agony with everyone
else in hot pursuit.
Sacred Tree: Upper Strata\nAbove the Clouds
I won't permit you to get in my way,\n{player_name}.
I know where you're coming from and \nwhat you're trying to do, Nedrick, but\nyou're going about things the wrong way.
If you're allowed to continue, countless\npeople will suffer. I can't let that happen.
Even if it costs my life, I WILL stop you.
Hollow words from a hollow man.\nFine, then. Do it if you can.
If the creator of the world—the Progenitor—\nis brought back, all possibility will vanish.
Nedrick wanted to save the world from this\nfate, so he sought power from Bahamut.
I share his dream, but his methods\nwill cost far too many innocent lives.
Whatever it takes, I can't let that happen!
I'd hoped to wrap this up in a single blow,\nbut good on you for surviving. That said...
You have strength to spare, along with\nwisdom, a strong will, and a dream.
Jinlorda said you were born powerless—\nthat you know the sting of such pain.
So why are you trying to do something\nthat will hurt countless innocents?!
I told you once that pretty words\nand deeds save nothing.
So long as you have no way to fight back\nagainst the Progenitor, anything you say\nis merely wasted air.
And if your thinking is truly so small,\nyou won't even be able to stop ME!
Throw as many bodies at me as you wish.\nThe result will remain the same.
His pact with Bahamut has increased his\npower exponentially. I don't have a single\nclue how to stand against him.
Yet Nedrick was not the only one to swear\na pact, so I shall stop him with MY ability!
I beseech you now, Bahamut!\nLend me your power!
Fools! Did you think you had a chance?\nYou'll never be able to best me with a\nmere fragment of Bahamut's power.

I pity you, Zethia. Despite forcibly making
a pact, you cannot even shapeshift.
Producing a duplicate with mana is the
best you can hope to do.
Fragment or no—pity or no—I shall give\nall that I am to defeating you, Nedrick!
Then witness the true power of Bahamut!
O Wyrm of Genesis! I call now upon\nthe power of the pact!
Now taste his power for yourself!
Do you see the truth of it now, Zethia?\nBahamut is too much for you alone.
Now relinquish the pact to me.\nThat is the way—the ONLY way—\nto oppose the Progenitor.
I cannot. I could never stand by and watch\nknowing that you intend to hurt so many!
Then your plan is to simply sit on your\nhands and sadly rue the downfall of all\npossibility at the hands of the Progenitor?
How can you not see your stupidity?!
YOU'RE the one who doesn't see the\nstupidity of your actions, Nedrick!
You say our desire to fight the Progenitor\nwithout harming people is nothing but\npretty words, and maybe that's true...
But those pretty words ARE possibility!\nThe ultimate possibility is the ability to\nsay, ＂I wish this is how things were.＂
You're trying so hard to protect possibility\nfrom the Progenitor, yet you turn around\nand deny it in the same breath!
It's madness! Don't you see that?!
Clever words from a hollow man!\nFine, then. Show me such possibility\nby saving that of the world's.
Possibility isn't fair. People with power\nswim in choices while those with none\nlack even the most basic rights.
If you have possibility greater than mine,\nbest me here and now.
If you cannot, then all of your words are\nnothing but a dream—and the hollow man\nwill die a hollow death!
We can't take another hit from him.
I'd love to say I have some clever plan\nup my sleeve, but this time...
It's over. This will finish it and... Gah?!
Guys, look! He's hurtin' for certain!
Though I'm loath to say it...I must depart...
I don't understand what's happening,\nbut I have no intention of abandoning you!
Okay, what the heck was THAT?!
There appears to be something very wrong\nwith his body...
I know that sensation. It appears the pact\nwith Bahamut had an ill effect on Nedrick's\nbody as well.
Then this is our chance; if we miss this\nopportunity, we may not be able to\ndefeat him again.
I hear what you're saying, but...
But it isn't fair? Of course it isn't.\nBut fairness and honor mean nothing\nin the face of the fate of the world.
Come on, everyone. We're going after him.
